FBIS4-18658 "drweu068_h_94003" FBIS-WEU-94-068 Daily Report 8 Apr 1994 GERMANY Bavaria To Deport 20 Kurds to Turkey Bavaria To Deport 20 Kurds to Turkey Discussion With Bonn AU0804133294 Berlin DIE WELT in German 8 Apr 94 p 3 AU0804133294 Berlin DIE WELT German BFN [Report by Hannes Burger: "Bavaria Deports Militant Kurds Again"] [Excerpt] Munich -- Bavaria has again issued deportation orders for five Kurds. This was announced yesterday by the Interior Ministry. More deportations are planned. Thus, orders have been issued for eight of the 13 arrested Kurds who participated in the Augsburg riots three weeks ago. Bavarian Interior Minister Guenther Beckstein (Christian Social Union) wants to discuss the deportation of militant Kurds in Bonn today and to speak in "very plain terms" with the government, particularly with Justice Minister Leutheusser-Schnarrenberger (Free Democratic Party of Germany). She has criticized the planned deportations in Bavaria. [passage omitted]
